author: felicity
msg: bug 1869: came up with a kluge for the "tokens have 16-bit atime" problem.
if the expire code detects that scancount is > 65535, reset all the
counters to an atime of 0.  it means one expire run doesn't actually
expire anything, but it should keep the useful tokens around instead of
the semi-random expire that was occuring in earlier versions.
